</div>
</div>
<p><a name="Health_benefits_ascribed_to_yogasana_practice" id="Health_benefits_ascribed_to_yogasana_practice"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hatha_yoga&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Health benefits ascribed to yogasana practice">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Health benefits ascribed to yogasana practice</span></h2>
<p>Different asanas are recommended by practitioners to cure or prevent problems ranging from constipation to cancer. It is known to reduce stress and other mental worries.<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since August 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup></p>
<p>See <a href="/wiki/Yoga_(alternative_medicine)" title="Yoga (alternative medicine)" class="mw-redirect">Yoga (alternative medicine)</a></p>
<p><a name="In_the_West" id="In_the_West"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Hatha_yoga&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: In the West">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">In the West</span></h2>
<div class="rellink noprint relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Yoga_as_exercise" title="Yoga as exercise" class="mw-redirect">Yoga as exercise</a></div>
<p>The 2005 "Yoga in America" survey, conducted by <a href="/wiki/Yoga_Journal" title="Yoga Journal">Yoga Journal</a>, shows that the number of practitioners in the US increased to 16.5 million with the 18-24 age group, showing a 46% increase in one year.<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
